        <num>CC 1774</num>
        <heading>1774.  Time for fulfillment of condition that an event shall not occur</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1774.  Time for fulfillment of condition that an event shall not occur
If the condition is that an event shall not occur within a fixed time, it is considered as fulfilled once that time has elapsed without the event having occurred.
The condition is regarded as fulfilled whenever it is certain that the event will not occur, whether or not a time has been fixed.</p>
        </content>
